Assignment 3 - Cloning a R repository.

  1. Clone this GitHub repository to your local Rstudio. To do this you need to:

    1. Navigate to the GitHub repository

    2. Copy the SSH key under Code >> SSH as shown below.

    4. In Rstudio Click New Project

    6. Select Version Control

    8. Select Git

    10. Paste the repository url you copies from GitHub git@github.com:dzvoti/TFNC-Training.git

    11. Give your project directory(folder) a name (Best to use same name as repo) and tell git where to place the folder

    13. Rstudio is now synced with GitHub and you can see your files in Rstudio
